I’ve been injured and out of the water for over 4 weeks now. The pain started over 6 weeks ago, but I wasn’t listening to my body and continued to surf, which just made things worse. I plan to fly back to Germany next week for the next 4 weeks to get proper care and physical therapy. It’s been hard mentally and physically. Surfing is my life and not being able to do it or any physical activity for a few weeks definitely took a toll. But I’m ready to start recovering and I’m looking forward to getting back🫶. Here’s just some pictures from a trip I’m reminiscing on right now🥰. 

Photos by @juan_medina_jcm 📸

What a year🙌
Saw so many beautiful places, met incredible new people, and learned some important lessons. 2023 definitely had its ups and down, but I’m finishing the year on a high note, and I feel ready and excited to start 2024❤️.
Happy New Year everyone🥰

#happynewyear #2023 #2024 #newyear #family #friends #travelinspo #travelgram #learning #nature #beautifuldestinations #love #happiness #goodvibes #goodenergy #manifesting #2024willbemyyear

9 years ago I was approached to partner with Hurley. I was only 12 years old and over the moon about it. The brand always fascinated me, and I loved wearing their clothing, and meeting their team riders. Starting this year I say good bye. @hurley thank you for all the love and support you’ve given me. The Hurley team was like family. Moving forward I’m very excited for new opportunities and for what 2024 has in store for me🥰.
